-- 2010-06-28T07:12:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/takashimaya-to-end-u-s-operations-to-focus-on-asia-sells-new-york-assets.html

          
          
             Takashimaya Co., a Japanese
department-store operator, said it plans to terminate its U.S.
operations to relocate resources to faster-growing markets in
Asia.  
 The company will sell a property on New Yorkâ€™s Fifth Avenue
to a unit of Thor Equities LLC for $142 million and book a one-
time gain of 11 billion yen this fiscal year from the sale,
according to a statement to the Tokyo Stock Exchange today.  
